#: ../../api/saves.md:1
msgid "Saves and event sourcing"
msgstr "Sauvegardes et event sourcing"

#: ../../api/saves.md:3
msgid "`axiom.savestore`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.savestore:1 of
msgid "axiom.savestore — saves stored separately from the universe."
msgstr "axiom.savestore — sauvegardes stockées séparément de l'univers."

#: axiom.savestore:3 of
msgid ""
"The source tree (and its compiled cache) is the universe **definition**; "
"play-throughs live in dedicated databases::"
msgstr ""
"L'arborescence source (et son cache compilé) est la **définition** de "
"l'univers ; les parties vivent dans des bases dédiées ::"

#: axiom.savestore:10 of
msgid ""
"Each save db is **self-contained** — full schema, with a **copy of the "
"definition tables** taken at creation. Benefits:"
msgstr ""
"Chaque base de save est **autonome** — schéma complet, avec une **copie "
"des tables de définition** prise à la création. Avantages :"

#: axiom.savestore:13 of
msgid "`Session` and the whole engine work unchanged (a single DB path);"
msgstr ""
"`Session` et tout le moteur fonctionnent inchangés (un seul chemin de "
"base) ;"

#: axiom.savestore:14 of
msgid ""
"patching the universe does not brick the games (they keep their own "
"definition, resynchronised on open via `refresh_definition` — in-place, "
"runtime entities and game state survive);"
msgstr ""
"patcher l'univers ne brique pas les parties (elles gardent leur propre "
"définition, resynchronisée à l'ouverture via `refresh_definition` — in-"
"place, les entités runtime et l'état de jeu survivent) ;"

#: axiom.savestore:17 of
msgid "one save = one portable file (trivial export/import)."
msgstr "une save = un fichier portable (export/import trivial)."

#: axiom.savestore:19 of
msgid ""
"Backward compatibility: historical saves embedded in the universe `.db` "
"remain listed and playable as-is (`storage='embedded'`). Only **new** "
"saves are created as separate files."
msgstr ""
"Rétrocompatibilité : les saves historiques embarquées dans le `.db` "
"univers restent listées et jouables telles quelles "
"(`storage='embedded'`). Seules les **nouvelles** saves sont créées en "
"fichiers séparés."

#: axiom.savestore:23 of
msgid "Zero Qt dependency: pure engine."
msgstr "Zéro dépendance Qt : moteur pur."

#: axiom.savestore.SaveStoreError:1 of
msgid "Error from the separate-save store."
msgstr "Erreur du magasin de sauvegardes séparées."

#: axiom.savestore.assets_dir_for_save:1 of
msgid "A save's illustrations folder (not created if missing)."
msgstr "Dossier des illustrations d'une save (non créé s'il n'existe pas)."

