msgstr "Type de retour"

#: axiom.savestore.copy_save_assets:1 of
msgid "Copy one save's illustrations to another. Returns the number copied."
msgstr ""
"Copie les illustrations d'une save vers une autre. Retourne le nombre "
"copié."

#: axiom.savestore.delete_save_assets:1 of
msgid "Delete a save's illustrations folder (no-op if missing)."
msgstr "Supprime le dossier d'illustrations d'une save (no-op s'il n'existe pas)."

#: axiom.savestore.truncate_save_assets:1 of
msgid "Purge the `turn_<n>.png` files with n > `last_kept_turn_id` (rewind)."
msgstr "Purge les fichiers `turn_<n>.png` avec n > `last_kept_turn_id` (rewind)."

#: axiom.savestore.truncate_save_assets:3 of
msgid "Returns the number of deleted files. Non-conforming names are ignored."
msgstr ""
"Retourne le nombre de fichiers supprimés. Les noms non conformes sont "
"ignorés."

#: axiom.savestore.truncate_assets_in:1 of
msgid ""
"Variant of `truncate_save_assets` on an explicit folder (Session with an "
"injected data_dir)."
msgstr ""
"Variante de `truncate_save_assets` sur un dossier explicite (Session avec"
" data_dir injecté)."

#: axiom.savestore.universe_key:1 of
msgid "Stable key of a universe, used to file its saves."
msgstr "Clé stable d'un univers, utilisée pour ranger ses saves."

#: axiom.savestore.universe_key:3 of
msgid ""
"Folder universe: name of the source folder. Flat `.db`: file stem. Based "
"on the **shape of the path** only (not on universe.toml existing): the "
"key must stay identical even when the source is momentarily "
"missing/broken, otherwise the saves become unreachable."
msgstr ""
"Univers-dossier : nom du dossier source. `.db` plat : stem du fichier. "
"Fondée sur la **forme du chemin** uniquement (pas sur l'existence de "
"universe.toml) : la clé doit rester identique même quand la source est "
"momentanément absente/cassée, sinon les saves deviennent introuvables."

#: axiom.savestore.saves_dir_for:1 of
msgid "A universe's separate-saves folder (not created if missing)."
msgstr "Dossier des saves séparées d'un univers (non créé s'il n'existe pas)."

#: axiom.savestore.is_separated_save_db:1 of
msgid "True when `db_path` is a separate save (carries a Save_Meta table)."
msgstr "True quand `db_path` est une save séparée (porte une table Save_Meta)."

#: axiom.savestore.create_save:1 of
msgid "Create a new game in its own `saves/<universe>/save_<uuid>.db` database."
msgstr ""
"Crée une nouvelle partie dans sa propre base "
"`saves/<universe>/save_<uuid>.db`."

#: axiom.savestore.create_save:3 of
msgid ""
"The universe definition is copied into the save db (self-contained). The "
"link to the universe (db + optional source) is recorded in `Save_Meta` "
"for resynchronisation on open."
msgstr ""
"La définition de l'univers est copiée dans la base de save (autonome). Le"
" lien vers l'univers (db + source éventuelle) est consigné dans "
"`Save_Meta` pour la resynchronisation à l'ouverture."

#: ../../api/saves.md
msgid "Returns"
msgstr "Renvoie"

#: axiom.savestore.create_save:7 of
msgid ""
"A dict with keys save_id and db_path — db_path is the database to hand to"
" `Session` (and to the engine helpers) to play this game."
msgstr ""
"Un dict avec les clés save_id et db_path — db_path est la base à passer à"
" `Session` (et aux helpers moteur) pour jouer cette partie."

#: axiom.savestore.new_save_container:1 of
msgid "Prepare a blank save db (definition copied + Save_Meta, no Saves row)."
msgstr ""
"Prépare une base de save vierge (définition copiée + Save_Meta, aucune "
"ligne Saves)."

#: axiom.savestore.new_save_container:3 of
msgid ""
"Common building block of `create_save` and of the imports (`save-import`,"
" `save-unpack`): the caller then creates/imports its Saves row(s) and "
"calls `finalize_save_container`."
msgstr ""
"Brique commune de `create_save` et des imports (`save-import`, `save-"
"unpack`) : l'appelant y crée/importe ensuite sa ou ses lignes Saves, puis"
" appelle `finalize_save_container`."

#: axiom.savestore.finalize_save_container:1 of
msgid "Rename a save container to its real save_id, definitively."
msgstr "Renomme définitivement un conteneur de save sur son save_id réel."

#: axiom.savestore.finalize_save_container:3 of
msgid ""
"Flushes the WAL into the main file BEFORE the rename (otherwise the "
"-wal/-shm sidecars would stay attached to the old name and the last "
"writes would be lost)."
msgstr ""
"Vide le WAL dans le fichier principal AVANT le renommage (sinon les "
"sidecars -wal/-shm resteraient attachés à l'ancien nom et les dernières "
"écritures seraient perdues)."

#: axiom.savestore.list_saves:1 of
msgid "List all the games of a universe, separate **and** embedded (legacy)."
msgstr ""
"Liste toutes les parties d'un univers, séparées **et** embarquées "
"(legacy)."

#: axiom.savestore.list_saves:3 of
msgid ""
"List of dicts in the `db_helpers.load_saves` format, enriched with "
"`db_path` (the database to open for this save) and `storage` ('separated'"
" | 'embedded'), sorted by `last_updated`, most recent first."
msgstr ""
"Liste de dicts au format de `db_helpers.load_saves`, enrichis de "
"`db_path` (la base à ouvrir pour cette save) et `storage` ('separated' | "
"'embedded'), triée par `last_updated`, plus récent d'abord."

#: axiom.savestore.resolve_save_db:1 of
msgid ""
"Return the database containing `save_id` (separate, or the universe "
"itself)."
msgstr "Retourne la base contenant `save_id` (séparée, ou l'univers lui-même)."

#: axiom.savestore.prepare_save_for_play:1 of
msgid "Resolve a save's database and resync its definition if the source changed."
msgstr ""
"Résout la base d'une save et resynchronise sa définition si la source a "
"changé."

#: axiom.savestore.prepare_save_for_play:3 of
msgid ""
"For a separate save linked to a folder universe: when the source hash "
"differs from the recorded one, `refresh_definition` is applied **to the "
"save db** (in-place: journal, runtime entities and game state intact) and"
" the recorded hash is updated. A missing/broken source is not blocking: "
"the save keeps its embedded definition (it is self-contained)."
msgstr ""
"Pour une save séparée liée à un univers-dossier : quand le hash de la "
"source diffère de celui consigné, `refresh_definition` est appliqué **à "
"la base de save** (in-place : journal, entités runtime et état de jeu "
"intacts) puis le hash consigné est mis à jour. Une source absente/cassée "
"n'est pas bloquante : la save garde sa définition embarquée (elle est "
"autonome)."

#: axiom.savestore.prepare_save_for_play:9 of
msgid ""
"The path of the database to hand to `Session`, or None for an unknown "
"save."
msgstr "Le chemin de la base à passer à `Session`, ou None pour une save inconnue."

#: axiom.savestore.refresh_save_definition:1 of
msgid "Resynchronise a separate save's definition from its universe source."
msgstr "Resynchronise la définition d'une save séparée depuis sa source univers."

#: axiom.savestore.refresh_save_definition:3 of
msgid ""
"No-op (False) for an embedded save, a save with no linked source, or one "
"already up to date. A malformed source is ignored (the save stays "
"playable as-is)."
msgstr ""
"No-op (False) pour une save embarquée, une save sans source liée, ou déjà"
" à jour. Une source malformée est ignorée (la save reste jouable telle "
"quelle)."

#: axiom.savestore.extract_save:1 of
msgid "Extract an **embedded** (legacy) save to its own separate file."
msgstr "Extrait une save **embarquée** (legacy) vers son propre fichier séparé."

#: axiom.savestore.extract_save:3 of
msgid ""
"Copies the universe's current definition + all this save's runtime rows. "
"The original save stays intact in the universe `.db` (it is a copy, not a"
" move)."
msgstr ""
"Copie la définition courante de l'univers + toutes les lignes runtime de "
"cette save. La save d'origine reste intacte dans le `.db` univers (c'est "
"une copie, pas un déplacement)."

#: axiom.savestore.extract_save:7 of
msgid "The path of the new `saves/<universe>/save_<id>.db` file."
msgstr "Le chemin du nouveau fichier `saves/<universe>/save_<id>.db`."

#: axiom.savestore.pack_save:1 of
msgid ""
"Export a save to a `.axiomsave` archive (zip: self-contained save.db + "
"manifest)."
msgstr ""
"Exporte une save en archive `.axiomsave` (zip : save.db autonome + "
"manifeste)."

#: axiom.savestore.pack_save:3 of
msgid ""
"A separate save is zipped as-is; an embedded (legacy) save is first "
"extracted to a self-contained file (a copy — the original stays). The "
"vector memory does not travel (empty on import)."
msgstr ""
"Une save séparée est zippée telle quelle ; une save embarquée (legacy) "
"est d'abord extraite vers un fichier autonome (une copie — l'original "
"reste). La mémoire vectorielle ne voyage pas (vide à l'import)."

#: axiom.savestore.unpack_save:1 of
msgid "Import a `.axiomsave` archive into a universe's save store."
msgstr "Importe une archive `.axiomsave` dans le magasin de saves d'un univers."

#: axiom.savestore.unpack_save:3 of
msgid ""
"By default, refuses an archive coming from another universe (different "
"`universe_key`) — pass `force=True` to override. When the `save_id` "
"already exists here, the imported save is **re-identified** (new uuid) so"
" an existing game is never overwritten."
msgstr ""
"Par défaut, refuse une archive issue d'un autre univers (`universe_key` "
"différente) — passer `force=True` pour outrepasser. Quand le `save_id` "
"existe déjà ici, la save importée est **ré-identifiée** (nouvel uuid) "
"pour ne jamais écraser une partie existante."

#: axiom.savestore.duplicate_save:8 axiom.savestore.unpack_save:8 of
msgid "A dict with keys save_id and db_path."
msgstr "Un dict avec les clés save_id et db_path."

#: axiom.savestore.duplicate_save:1 of
msgid "Duplicate a game as-is (full journal preserved)."
msgstr "Duplique une partie telle quelle (journal complet préservé)."

#: axiom.savestore.duplicate_save:3 of
msgid ""
"Separate save: re-identified file copy (new uuid) — the \"one save = one "
"file\" model is preserved, unlike a `fork_save` within the same file. "
"Embedded (legacy) save: fork at the last turn in the same database, as "
"before."
msgstr ""
"Save séparée : copie du fichier ré-identifiée (nouvel uuid) — le modèle «"
" une save = un fichier » est conservé, contrairement à un `fork_save` "
"dans le même fichier. Save embarquée (legacy) : fork au dernier tour dans"
" la même base, comme avant."

#: axiom.savestore.delete_save:1 of
msgid ""
"Delete a game. A separate save whose database becomes empty is removed "
"from disk."
msgstr ""
"Supprime une partie. Une save séparée dont la base se vide est effacée du"
" disque."

#: axiom.savestore.delete_save:3 of
msgid "True when a save was deleted."
msgstr "True quand une save a été supprimée."

#: axiom.savestore.delete_universe_saves:1 of
msgid ""
"Delete a universe's separate-saves folder (along with the universe), "
"illustrations included."
msgstr ""
"Supprime le dossier de saves séparées d'un univers (avec l'univers), "
"illustrations comprises."

#: ../../api/saves.md:10
msgid "`axiom.saves`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.saves:1 of
msgid "axiom.saves — save editing (creatable/editable by humans or LLMs)."
msgstr ""
"axiom.saves — édition de sauvegardes (créables/modifiables par humain ou "
"LLM)."

#: axiom.saves:3 of
msgid "Design decisions:"
msgstr "Décisions de conception :"

#: axiom.saves:5 of
msgid ""
"**D1**: the `Event_Log` journal stays the **source of truth** (it powers "
"the rewind). Editing happens *on top of it*: the state is "
"**materialised** at a point (replay), **forked** (truncated journal), and"
" an edited state is **imported** as a **new** save (\"genesis\" events at"
" turn 0). Derived data (State_Cache/Snapshots) is never edited directly."
msgstr ""
"**D1** : le journal `Event_Log` reste la **source de vérité** (il fait "
"tourner le rewind). L'édition se fait *par-dessus* : l'état est "
"**matérialisé** à un point (replay), **forké** (journal tronqué), et un "
"état édité est **importé** comme une **nouvelle** save (événements « "
"genèse » au tour 0). Les données dérivées (State_Cache/Snapshots) ne sont"
" jamais éditées directement."

#: axiom.saves:10 of
msgid ""
"**D3**: an imported save starts with an **empty vector memory** (it fills"
" up as you play)."
msgstr ""
"**D3** : une save importée démarre avec une **mémoire vectorielle vide** "
"(elle se remplit en jouant)."

#: axiom.saves:13 of
msgid ""
"Point selector: by **turn** (`at_turn`) or by **in-game time in minutes**"
" (`at_minute`, resolved through the `Timeline` table). Zero Qt "
"dependency."
msgstr ""
"Sélecteur de point : par **tour** (`at_turn`) ou par **temps in-game en "
"minutes** (`at_minute`, résolu via la table `Timeline`). Zéro dépendance "
"Qt."

#: axiom.saves:16 of
msgid "Editable text format, `save_state.toml`::"
msgstr "Format texte éditable, `save_state.toml` ::"

#: axiom.saves.SaveError:1 of
msgid "Save editing/reading error."
msgstr "Erreur d'édition/lecture de sauvegarde."

#: axiom.saves.resolve_point:1 of
msgid "Resolve a selector (turn or in-game minute) into a `turn_id`."
msgstr "Résout un sélecteur (tour ou minute in-game) en `turn_id`."

#: axiom.saves.resolve_point:3 of
msgid "`at_turn`: used as-is."
msgstr "`at_turn` : utilisé tel quel."

#: axiom.saves.resolve_point:4 of
msgid "`at_minute`: last turn whose `Timeline.in_game_time <= at_minute`."
msgstr "`at_minute` : dernier tour dont `Timeline.in_game_time <= at_minute`."

#: axiom.saves.resolve_point:5 of
msgid "neither: last turn of the save."
msgstr "aucun des deux : dernier tour de la save."

#: axiom.saves.materialize_state:1 of
msgid "Materialise a save's state at a given point (by replaying the journal)."
msgstr "Matérialise l'état d'une save à un point donné (en rejouant le journal)."

#: axiom.saves.materialize_state:3 of
msgid ""
"Per-entity stats = the universe's base stats (`Entity_Stats`) overlaid "
"with the state replayed up to the point (logical `State_Cache`). "
"Inventory and modifiers are the current state (tables that are not event-"
"sourced)."
msgstr ""
"Stats par entité = stats de base de l'univers (`Entity_Stats`) "
"recouvertes par l'état rejoué jusqu'au point (`State_Cache` logique). "
"L'inventaire et les modificateurs sont l'état courant (tables non event-"
"sourcées)."

#: axiom.saves.export_save_state:1 of
msgid "Export a save's materialised state to an editable `save_state.toml`."
msgstr "Exporte l'état matérialisé d'une save vers un `save_state.toml` éditable."

#: axiom.saves.import_save_state:1 of
msgid "Create a **new** playable save from a `save_state.toml`."
msgstr "Crée une **nouvelle** save jouable à partir d'un `save_state.toml`."

#: axiom.saves.import_save_state:3 of
msgid ""
"Seeds the state through \"genesis\" events at turn 0 (entity_create + "
"stat_set), then materialises State_Cache, the inventory, the modifiers "
"and a Timeline entry. Empty vector memory. Returns the new save_id."
msgstr ""
"Sème l'état via des événements « genèse » au tour 0 (entity_create + "
"stat_set), puis matérialise State_Cache, l'inventaire, les modificateurs "
"et une entrée Timeline. Mémoire vectorielle vide. Retourne le nouveau "
"save_id."

#: axiom.saves.apply_correction:1 of
msgid "Apply a correction to an **existing** save without rewriting the past."
msgstr "Applique une correction à une save **existante** sans réécrire le passé."

#: axiom.saves.apply_correction:3 of
msgid ""
"Stat changes become `manual_edit` events (at the chosen turn, default = "
"last turn) — the journal stays consistent and append-only, the rewind is "
"preserved, and the edit is traceable. Inventory and modifiers (not event-"
"sourced) are written directly."
msgstr ""
"Les changements de stats deviennent des événements `manual_edit` (au tour"
" choisi, défaut = dernier tour) — le journal reste cohérent et append-"
"only, le rewind est préservé, et l'édition est traçable. L'inventaire et "
"les modificateurs (non event-sourcés) sont écrits directement."

#: axiom.saves.apply_correction:8 of
msgid "The `patch` dict has the shape::"
msgstr "Le dict `patch` a la forme ::"

#: axiom.saves.apply_correction:16 of
msgid "The `turn_id` the correction was appended at."
msgstr "Le `turn_id` auquel la correction a été apposée."

#: axiom.saves.diff_save_states:1 of
msgid "Compute the correction patch between two parsed `save_state.toml` states."
msgstr "Calcule le patch de correction entre deux états `save_state.toml` parsés."

#: axiom.saves.diff_save_states:3 of
msgid ""
"Supports the \"edit the save\" flow: the state is exported, the user "
"edits the TOML, and only the **differences** are appended via "
"`apply_correction` (otherwise every unchanged stat would become a "
"spurious `manual_edit` event)."
msgstr ""
"Sert au flux « éditer la save » : l'état est exporté, l'utilisateur "
"modifie le TOML, et seules les **différences** sont apposées via "
"`apply_correction` (sinon chaque stat inchangée deviendrait un événement "
"`manual_edit` parasite)."

#: axiom.saves.diff_save_states:8 of
msgid ""
"stats: changed or added values (removing a stat does not exist in the "
"correction model — ignored);"
msgstr ""
"stats : valeurs modifiées ou ajoutées (la suppression d'une stat n'existe"
" pas dans le modèle de correction — ignorée) ;"

#: axiom.saves.diff_save_states:10 of
msgid ""
"inventory: changed/added quantities; a vanished line means quantity 0 (= "
"removal);"
msgstr ""
"inventaire : quantités modifiées/ajoutées ; une ligne disparue signifie "
"quantité 0 (= retrait) ;"

#: axiom.saves.diff_save_states:12 of
msgid ""
"modifiers: only **new** ones are kept (a correction can only add "
"modifiers)."
msgstr ""
"modificateurs : seuls les **nouveaux** sont retenus (une correction ne "
"sait qu'ajouter des modificateurs)."

#: axiom.saves.apply_correction_file:1 of
msgid ""
"Load a TOML file (same sections as save_state.toml) and apply it as a "
"correction."
msgstr ""
"Charge un fichier TOML (mêmes sections que save_state.toml) et l'applique"
" en correction."

#: axiom.saves.fork_save:1 of
msgid "Create a new save = `save_id`'s journal **truncated** at the chosen point."
msgstr ""
"Crée une nouvelle save = le journal de `save_id` **tronqué** au point "
"choisi."

#: axiom.saves.fork_save:3 of
msgid ""
"The full journal up to the point is copied (rewind/audit preserved); "
"current inventory and modifiers are copied as-is. Returns the new "
"save_id."
msgstr ""
"Le journal complet jusqu'au point est copié (rewind/audit préservés) ; "
"l'inventaire et les modificateurs courants sont copiés tels quels. "
"Retourne le nouveau save_id."

#: ../../api/saves.md:17
msgid "`axiom.checkpoint`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint:1 of
msgid "database/checkpoint.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint:3 of
msgid "Checkpoint and rewind management for Axiom AI saves."
msgstr "Gestion des checkpoints et du rewind pour les sauvegardes d'Axiom AI."

#: axiom.checkpoint:5 of
msgid ""
"The CheckpointManager exposes the rewind primitive (deleting future "
"events and rebuilding the State_Cache), a save listing helper, and the "
"destructive Hardcore-mode save deletion."
msgstr ""
"Le CheckpointManager expose la primitive de rewind (suppression des "
"événements futurs et reconstruction du State_Cache), un helper de listage"
" des saves, et la suppression destructive du mode Hardcore."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager:1 of
msgid "Manages save checkpoints, rewinds, and Hardcore deletion for one universe."
msgstr "Gère les checkpoints, rewinds et la suppression Hardcore pour un univers."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager:3 axiom.events.EventSourcer:4 of
msgid ""
"Filesystem path to an existing universe .db file created by "
"database.schema.create_universe_db()."
msgstr ""
"Chemin de fichier d'un `.db` univers existant créé par "
"database.schema.create_universe_db()."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:1 of
msgid "Revert a save to its state at target_turn_id."
msgstr "Ramène une save à son état au tour target_turn_id."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:3 of
msgid ""
"Comprehensive and atomic: in a single transaction it removes everything "
"recorded after the target turn and rebuilds every derived view to its "
"turn-N state:"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:7 of
#, fuzzy
msgid "Count the future events to delete (for the summary)."
msgstr "Compter combien d'événements futurs seront supprimés (pour le résumé)."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:8 of
msgid ""
"DELETE the future ``Event_Log`` rows, plus the ``Snapshots`` and "
"``Timeline`` rows for later turns."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:10 of
msgid ""
"Roll back living-mode memory: future ``Facts`` are dropped, beliefs are "
"recomputed from their surviving sources "
"(:func:`axiom.observations.rollback_observations`) and mental models "
"created after the target are dropped / flagged stale "
"(:func:`axiom.mental_models.rollback_mental_models`)."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:15 of
msgid ""
"Restore temporary modifiers (buffs/debuffs) to their turn-N state from "
"the per-turn snapshot (:func:`axiom.modifiers.rollback_modifiers`) — they"
" decay in minutes and are not event-sourced, so they cannot be replayed."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:19 of
msgid ""
"Un-fire scheduled events that fired after the target turn, so they can "
"trigger again when the clock re-crosses their minute."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:21 of
#, fuzzy
msgid "Rebuild ``State_Cache`` from the surviving events."
msgstr "Reconstruire le State_Cache depuis les événements survivants."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:23 of
msgid ""
"Note: the semantic memory store is a separate concern, rolled back by the"
" caller via :meth:`axiom.memory.VectorMemory.rollback`."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:26 of
msgid "The save to rewind."
msgstr "La save à rembobiner."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:27 of
msgid ""
"The turn to revert to (inclusive).  All events with turn_id strictly "
"greater than this value are permanently removed."
msgstr ""
"Le tour auquel revenir (inclus).  Tous les événements dont le turn_id est"
" strictement supérieur à cette valeur sont définitivement supprimés."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:31 of
msgid "A dict with keys deleted_events and rebuilt_to_turn."
msgstr "Un dict avec les clés deleted_events et rebuilt_to_turn."

#: ../../api/saves.md
msgid "Raises"
msgstr "Lève"

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:12
#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.list_checkpoints:11
#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.rewind:34
#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_current_stats:9 of
msgid "On any database failure."
msgstr "Sur tout échec de base de données."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.list_checkpoints:1 of
msgid "Return the distinct turn IDs present in Event_Log for a save, ascending."
msgstr ""
"Retourne les turn_id distincts présents dans Event_Log pour une save, "
"croissants."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.list_checkpoints:3 of
msgid ""
"This list represents the turns the player could rewind to.  The UI can "
"use it to populate a \"rewind to turn …\" selector."
msgstr ""
"Cette liste représente les tours vers lesquels le joueur peut rembobiner."
"  L'UI peut s'en servir pour remplir un sélecteur « rembobiner au tour… "
"»."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.list_checkpoints:6 of
msgid "The save whose checkpoint turns are requested."
msgstr "La save dont les tours de checkpoint sont demandés."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.list_checkpoints:8 of
msgid ""
"Sorted list of unique turn_id integers.  Empty list if the save has no "
"recorded events."
msgstr ""
"Liste triée de turn_id entiers uniques.  Liste vide si la save n'a aucun "
"événement enregistré."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:1 of
msgid "Irrevocably delete a save and its associated universe directory."
msgstr "Supprime irrévocablement une save et le dossier d'univers associé."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:3 of
msgid "Intended exclusively for Hardcore mode upon player death.  This method:"
msgstr ""
"Destiné exclusivement au mode Hardcore à la mort du joueur.  Cette "
"méthode :"

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:4 of
msgid "Removes the save row from the database (cascades to Event_Log, etc)."
msgstr "Supprime la ligne de save de la base (cascade vers Event_Log, etc)."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:5 of
msgid "Attempts to delete the universe_dir from the filesystem."
msgstr "Tente de supprimer le universe_dir du système de fichiers."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:7 of
msgid "The save to erase from the database."
msgstr "La save à effacer de la base."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:8 of
msgid "Absolute path to the universe directory to delete."
msgstr "Chemin absolu du dossier d'univers à supprimer."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:10 of
msgid "If the directory cannot be deleted after multiple retries."
msgstr "Si le dossier ne peut pas être supprimé après plusieurs tentatives."

#: axiom.checkpoint.CheckpointManager.delete_save:11 of
msgid "If universe_dir does not exist."
msgstr "Si universe_dir n'existe pas."

#: ../../api/saves.md:24
msgid "`axiom.events`"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:1 of
msgid "database/event_sourcing.py"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:3 of
msgid "Core Event Sourcing implementation for Axiom AI."
msgstr "Implémentation centrale de l'event sourcing d'Axiom AI."

#: axiom.events:5 of
msgid ""
"Every state change in the game is recorded as an immutable event in "
"Event_Log.  The State_Cache is a performance materialisation derived by "
"replaying those events.  This module is the authoritative bridge between "
"the two."
msgstr ""
"Chaque changement d'état du jeu est enregistré comme un événement "
"immuable dans Event_Log.  Le State_Cache est une matérialisation de "
"performance dérivée en rejouant ces événements.  Ce module est le pont de"
" référence entre les deux."

#: axiom.events:10 of
msgid "Supported event_type values (non-exhaustive; the engine is extensible):"
msgstr ""
"Valeurs d'event_type prises en charge (non exhaustif ; le moteur est "
"extensible) :"

#: axiom.events:11 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"'entity_create'  payload: {\"entity_id\": str, \"entity_type\": str, "
"\"name\": str}"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:12 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"'stat_change'    payload: {\"entity_id\": str, \"stat_key\": str, "
"\"delta\": float}"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:13 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid "OR {\"entity_id\": str, \"stat_key\": str, \"value\": str}"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:14 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"'stat_set'       payload: {\"entity_id\": str, \"stat_key\": str, "
"\"value\": str}"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:15 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"'dialogue'       payload: {\"speaker\": str, \"text\": str}   (no cache "
"mutation)"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events:16 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"'combat_roll'    payload: {\"entity_id\": str, ...}         (no cache "
"mutation)"
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer:1 of
msgid ""
"Manages event appending, querying, and State_Cache reconstruction for a "
"single Axiom AI universe database."
msgstr ""
"Gère l'ajout d'événements, leur interrogation et la reconstruction du "
"State_Cache pour une base d'univers Axiom AI."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.append_event:1 of
msgid "Insert a new event into Event_Log and return its auto-generated event_id."
msgstr ""
"Insère un nouvel événement dans Event_Log et retourne son event_id auto-"
"généré."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.update_event_payload:1 of
msgid ""
"Update the payload of an event identified by save_id, turn_id, and "
"event_type."
msgstr ""

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.append_events_batch:1 of
msgid "Insert multiple events in a single transaction."
msgstr "Insère plusieurs événements dans une seule transaction."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.append_events_batch:3 of
msgid "List of (save_id, turn_id, event_type, target_entity, payload) tuples."
msgstr "Liste de tuples (save_id, turn_id, event_type, target_entity, payload)."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_events:1 of
msgid "Fetch events for a save, ordered chronologically."
msgstr "Récupère les événements d'une save, par ordre chronologique."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_events:3 of
msgid "The save whose events are requested."
msgstr "La save dont les événements sont demandés."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_events:4 of
msgid "Only events with turn_id > this value are returned."
msgstr "Seuls les événements avec turn_id > cette valeur sont retournés."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_events:5 of
msgid ""
"If provided, only events with turn_id <= this value are returned.  None "
"means all future events."
msgstr ""
"Si fourni, seuls les événements avec turn_id <= cette valeur sont "
"retournés.  None signifie tous les événements futurs."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.rebuild_state_cache:1 of
msgid "Flush and rebuild State_Cache for a save by replaying Event_Log."
msgstr "Vide et reconstruit le State_Cache d'une save en rejouant Event_Log."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.rebuild_state_cache:3 of
msgid "The save whose cache is being rebuilt."
msgstr "La save dont le cache est reconstruit."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.rebuild_state_cache:4 of
msgid ""
"If provided, only events up to this turn are replayed.  None means the "
"full history."
msgstr ""
"Si fourni, seuls les événements jusqu'à ce tour sont rejoués.  None "
"signifie l'historique complet."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.rebuild_state_cache:6 of
msgid ""
"If True, ignores all snapshots and replays the entire history from turn "
"0.  Use this to fix cache corruption."
msgstr ""
"Si True, ignore tous les snapshots et rejoue l'historique entier depuis "
"le tour 0.  À utiliser pour réparer une corruption de cache."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.rebuild_state_cache:10 of
msgid ""
"Optimized to start from the nearest previous snapshot if one exists, "
"unless force_full=True."
msgstr ""
"Optimisé pour démarrer du snapshot précédent le plus proche s'il en "
"existe un, sauf si force_full=True."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.update_state_cache:1 of
msgid "Incrementally apply a just-appended batch of events to State_Cache."
msgstr ""
"Applique incrémentalement un lot d'événements tout juste ajoutés au "
"State_Cache."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.update_state_cache:3 of
msgid ""
"State_Cache is a materialised view of the base stats derived from "
"Event_Log.  rebuild_state_cache() replays the entire history (or from the"
" nearest snapshot); this method instead applies *only* the given batch on"
" top of the affected entities' current cached values, keeping the cache "
"fresh after each turn without an O(history) replay."
msgstr ""
"State_Cache est une vue matérialisée des stats de base dérivée "
"d'Event_Log.  rebuild_state_cache() rejoue l'historique entier (ou depuis"
" le snapshot le plus proche) ; cette méthode applique au contraire "
"*seulement* le lot donné par-dessus les valeurs en cache des entités "
"concernées, gardant le cache frais après chaque tour sans replay en "
"O(historique)."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.update_state_cache:9 of
msgid ""
"This is what keeps DB reads (the sidebar's load_full_game_state / "
"load_stats tasks, which read State_Cache) in sync with the changes a turn"
" just produced — see TICKET-002."
msgstr ""
"C'est ce qui garde les lectures de base (les tâches load_full_game_state "
"/ load_stats de la barre latérale, qui lisent State_Cache) synchronisées "
"avec les changements qu'un tour vient de produire — voir TICKET-002."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.update_state_cache:13 of
msgid "The save whose cache is being updated."
msgstr "La save dont le cache est mis à jour."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.update_state_cache:14 of
msgid ""
"List of (save_id, turn_id, event_type, target_entity, payload) tuples, in"
" the same shape as append_events_batch().  Only entity_create / "
"stat_change / stat_set events mutate the cache; all others are ignored."
msgstr ""
"Liste de tuples (save_id, turn_id, event_type, target_entity, payload), "
"de même forme que append_events_batch().  Seuls les événements "
"entity_create / stat_change / stat_set mutent le cache ; tous les autres "
"sont ignorés."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.validate_integrity:1 of
msgid "Verify that the current State_Cache matches a fresh replay of history."
msgstr ""
"Vérifie que le State_Cache courant correspond à un replay frais de "
"l'historique."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.validate_integrity:3 of
msgid ""
"This is a diagnostic tool to detect corruption in the materialised cache."
" It does NOT use snapshots."
msgstr ""
"C'est un outil de diagnostic pour détecter la corruption du cache "
"matérialisé. Il n'utilise PAS les snapshots."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.validate_integrity:6 of
msgid ""
"A (passed, mismatches) tuple — mismatches maps entity_id to a dict of "
"stat_key to (cached_val, actual_val) pairs."
msgstr ""
"Un tuple (passed, mismatches) — mismatches fait correspondre entity_id à "
"un dict de stat_key vers des paires (cached_val, actual_val)."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.state_at:1 of
msgid ""
"Compute the materialised state by replaying events, without touching the "
"DB."
msgstr ""
"Calcule l'état matérialisé en rejouant les événements, sans toucher à la "
"base."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.state_at:3 of
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Pure read: replays Event_Log (optionally up to a turn) and returns the "
"resulting `entity_id -> {stat_key: stat_value}` map. Used by snapshotting"
" and by the save editor (`axiom.saves`) to materialise state at any "
"point."
msgstr ""
"Lecture pure : rejoue Event_Log (éventuellement jusqu'à un tour) et "
"retourne la correspondance `entity_id -> {stat_key: stat_value}` "
"résultante. Utilisé par le snapshotting et par l'éditeur de saves "
"(`axiom.saves`) pour matérialiser l'état à n'importe quel point."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.take_snapshot:1 of
msgid "Capture the current materialised state and store it in Snapshots."
msgstr "Capture l'état matérialisé courant et le stocke dans Snapshots."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.take_snapshot:3 of
msgid ""
"This is an expensive operation (JSON-serialising the full state) and "
"should be called sparingly."
msgstr ""
"C'est une opération coûteuse (sérialisation JSON de l'état complet), à "
"appeler avec parcimonie."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_current_stats:1 of
msgid "Read the current materialised stats for one entity from State_Cache."
msgstr "Lit les stats matérialisées courantes d'une entité depuis le State_Cache."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_current_stats:3 of
msgid "The active save identifier."
msgstr "L'identifiant de la save active."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_current_stats:4 of
msgid "The entity whose stats are requested."
msgstr "L'entité dont les stats sont demandées."

#: axiom.events.EventSourcer.get_current_stats:6 of
msgid ""
"Dict mapping stat_key -> stat_value strings.  Empty dict if the entity "
"has no cached stats or does not exist."
msgstr ""
"Dict de stat_key -> stat_value (chaînes).  Dict vide si l'entité n'a pas "
"de stats en cache ou n'existe pas."

